case_body_condition: Not recognizable - Partial skeletal parts only
case_circumstances: Victim discovered 10/07/91 at the bottom of an embankment along Interstate 70, East Providence Township, Bedford County, Pennsylvania, near the village of Breezewood.  Though the remains were completely skeletonized, some artifacts (clothing, glasses, belt, shoes, wristwatch, coins, small flashlight and some hairs from the clothing) were recovered as well.  Anthropological examination reveals the Victim to have had prominent cheek bones and a flat face, and also suggests this Victim may be of mixed racial ancestory with a strong mongoloid component.  Case entered into ViCAP.  Please contact Pennsylvania State Police for all follow-up inquiries.
